    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix thread creation error handling in nfapi PNF module\n\n### Summary\nThe nfapi PNF module was silently failing to create critical receiver threads due to missing error checking on pthread_create calls. This caused the PHY layer to hang during initialization since expected threads were not running.\n\nThis fix adds proper error checking and logging for all pthread_create calls in the PNF module.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_pnf.c`: Added error checking for pthread_create in start_request, nr_start_request, configure_nr_nfapi_pnf, and configure_nfapi_pnf functions\n- Added appropriate error logging with strerror to show actual failure reasons\n- Functions returning int now properly return on thread creation failure\n- Void functions now conditionally execute dependent code only on successful thread creation\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Run OAI gNB with NFAPI PNF mode enabled\n2. Observe that despite no error messages, the PHY layer fails to initialize properly\n3. Using gdb, confirm that expected receiver threads are not running\n4. Check that pthread_create calls in nfapi_pnf.c are failing silently\n\nWith this fix, thread creation failures will be properly logged and handled, allowing for proper system initialization or clear error reporting.\n"
}